    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-03T18:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-03T18:14:00-05:00" n="100"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d100">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11G93/1007: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Belt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-03T18:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received February 4, 3.27 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s January 27, 6 p.m., my January 30, 9 a.m.<note n="8"
                        xml:id="d100fn8">Latter not printed.</note> Foreign Minister to-day informs
                    me Minister of Finance notifies him that to date there has been remitted to
                    London in various installments 80,000 pounds sterling in payment of the bonded
                    indebtedness of the railroad.</p>
                <p>He promises me memorandum <hi rend="italic">re</hi> issuance bonds tomorrow,
                    substance of which I will cable the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Belt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
